News headlines are sourced from GNews (https://gnews.io) under their developer terms.
NexOS ships with a bootstrap GNews developer-tier API key so the News tab works out-of-the-box;
this key remains the property of GNews and is subject to GNews's rate limits (100 req/day).
Users can rotate or replace the key from Settings → GNews API key.

Weather data is sourced from two providers:
  - OpenWeather (https://openweathermap.org) when a developer key is configured.
    NexOS ships with a bootstrap free-tier OpenWeather key so the Weather screen works
    out-of-the-box. The key is the property of OpenWeather and is subject to OpenWeather's
    free-tier rate limits (60 requests/minute). Users can rotate or replace the key in
    Settings → Weather provider.
  - Open-Meteo (https://open-meteo.com), licensed under CC-BY 4.0. Used as the no-key
    fallback. NexOS attributes Open-Meteo on the Weather screen as required by the licence.

